<br>
1.) Earth Pet; burnout II, expedience, 2 daggers, fire shield. (1 buff slot free to cancel snare, do this by casting see invis then canceling it once the rest of the buffs are on)<br>
2.) Me buffed (1 buff slot free to cancel snare)<br>
<br>
3.) If I know he is ubber buffed I will chain cast Cancel Magic until he realizes what is happening<br>
<br>
4.) Send in pet and chain cast malo. Hoping for a successful stick on malo.<br>
<br>
5.) wait for his snare to get pet, cancel magic (saving my staff of ruins for myself).<br>
<br>
6.) Keep chain casting malo until it sticks. Once it does wait for a successful root from pet.<br>
<br>
7.) If I am snared I will use my staff of ruins to cancel the effect. If I am snared again I am hoping I have enough time to get off a cancel magic before he is on me. If he is on me it is all over from there (unless pet gets a root while he is pounding me).<br>
<br>
8.) Once he is rooted I will wait and see how he reacts:<br>
a.) If he attacks my pet I will then heal my pet and let fireshield and pet do some damage and see how that goes to determine how well equiped/buffed the ranger is. If I see this working I will keep this up knowing that more and more roots will land allowing this to continue on.<br>
b.) If he starts casting cancel magic on  himself I will nuke hard with my heaviest nuke, knowing his root will go away anyways. Then I will kite him around waiting for another root to land and then start all over from there. <br>
<br>
Roamer TZ<br>
