<br>
2 things I always have when I know I am gonna pvp or duel...  Levitate and Summon companion.<br>
<br>
Levitate: run up a hill, run into the open field and start casting all you want.  No melee (without levi of course) will be able to hit you.<br>
<br>
Summon companion: always know where your pet is, and what is happening to it.   <p><FONT SIZE=5><b><i>Chrystall Nifelheim</FONT></b></i><BR><i>Mini Conjurer of <a href=http://www.draconictribe.com>Draconic tribe</a>, Reporting for CoH-duty, sir!!!</i><BR><i>Well... euh... You will have to wait till I made dwarf stew for my uber shammie</i></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujarariza.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarariza</A> at: 11/8/01 4:36:04 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uanguss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anguss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/01 5:33:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How are Mages in PvP?</span><hr size=1> one word:<br>
