<br>
Once you think you know a good strategy....<br>
<br>
(34 / 49th level bolts from OOR) You get your ass handed to you by a wizard with 180+ FR (at level 50 I have 240 FR FULLY buffed, I don't normally pk with that FR)<br>
<br>
Mages are like wizards.... We are the hunters.... you must be VERY aggressive.... go AFTER your enemy... odn't let him come to you.... <br>
<br>
Ok, now just to add a few of my own thoughts as a 50+ mage of SZ.<br>
<br>
Whether group or 1 on 1 combat.... if there is a bard against you... you are F'cked.... Nothing you can do about it.... the game is currently &quot;broken&quot; like this.... but that's ok... because with char/ Shockof line (many people have higher FR than MR) and annul magic you are still a valuable addition to a pking group....<br>
<br>
Despite belief to the contrary... Tested in the Arena against guildmates... the shock line does NOT interrupt spell casting.<br>
<br>
However... Elemental Maelstrom does.... Fight with an Enchanter... if they land a tashania (in pvp debuffs do 150% of normal) you are almost granted to land a malisement/malosi) (if you aren't level 60 and able to land an uresistable mala anyways, then the enchanter is slightly less vital, especially against a significantly lower opponent)<br>
<br>
Pets....<br>
<br>
Vocerate Fire is a great choice if you know you are fighting a rooting caster class (druid cleric shaman wizard) (although druids might snare instead of root /shrug [wizards almost always root... Snaring themselves would be VERY embarrasing](although I'm on team evil... so I've honestly never fought against a sk/necro outside of the arena)<br>
<br>
If I had an epic pet I would use it 100% of the time....<br>
<br>
but I don't... not yet anyways....<br>
<br>
51 earth pet is good too.... Roots ACTUALLY land more so than some people would have you believe... especially if they aren't pking with a cleric/shaman/druid/ (although this is RARE) to give them resist magic.<br>
<br>
And against a lower level opponent your earth pet is actually the BEST pet (barring the epic of course).  Roots land very easily upon someone lower level than your pet even with HIGH MR (100+ MR)<br>
<br>
Pet's are your best friend in cities... They won't aggro the guards.  Nukes will if you accidently cast too near an npc....<br>
Use this to your Advantage... get good faction and FORCE them to be near NPCS so that they can't cast/melee you<br>
<br>
Nukes.... Inside Char is really your only option (especially where you can't cast through walls)  Shock of x works too.... but the significantly longer cast time is a downer....<br>
<br>
I haven't gotten my Uber bolt yet.....<br>
<br>
But 49th bolt is pretty awesome too...  Kinda a pain indoors....<br>
<br>
BUT.... it IS doable to cast a 7 second LOS spell on someone.... just sometimes you gotta get lucky... try casting when they are out of your sight... and if they get into your sight by the time the spell finishes... then great.... if not... duck to interrupt...<br>
<br>
Keep a couple dagger of symbols (and now the new luclin summonings as well)<br>
<br>
Pets DO resist spells from time to time (especially later on) and giving them an additionaly 40 or so MR is GREAT...<br>
<br>
Don't play zone tag..... They have the advantage.... (well unless you are trying to escape a bard or something)<br>
<br>
<br>
ok... Classes...<br>
<br>
Bards.... Don't even try to fight them.... A good tactic to avoid them is levitate over water.... Anull their levitate song.... (if you beging levitating while already under water you can't actually get out of the water and will remain submerged for spellcasting purposes until you step up onto something) It's saved my life more than once while I was camping bloodgills.<br>
<br>
Druids....Winged Death is insane.... Don't fight a 54+ druid 1 on 1.... They WILL win....(unless of course you are really lucky and catch them WHILE they are quad kiting something =D One note... Druids have crappy FR compared to alot of other classes(although at later levels this doesn't apply)<br>
<br>
Wizards... You gotta be quick... No bolts allowed here... Lure spells will kill you no matter your resists.... Try to catch them in pve gear.... If you can catch them by surprise you actually have a shot of beating them....<br>
<br>
Monks.... If Equal speed (both have jboots)... Use levitate.... Jouste them..... Run around while your pet beats them up... If they get low... they will start to panic and start Feign Deathing...... Just spam /pet attack.... and med for nukes =D Monks have low resists until higher levels.... Use this to your advantage....<br>
<br>
Warriors.... Their resists are HIGH by this level.....  If they have a snare item... they can take your pet out of the equation.... And if they are smart will use Bow and Arrows on you... which have an INSANE range Just evade arrows like you would a bolt... if you were fighting a mage.  DESPITE the bow and arrows.... don't let them get in melee range.... I guarentee you their melee is better than their range weapon.  Weighted axe+ could theoretically hit you for 450 damage.. that's like a high level rogue backstab.... <br>
<br>
Rangers.... They'll use bow and Arrows Avoid them... Cast around corners.... Luckily they won't have as many HP as a warrior so are generally easier to take out.<br>
<br>
Pally... Give me a break.... Anyone's mother can survive a paladin 1 on 1... Just make sure you throw on as much MR as you can....(although throw in a druid to Winged Death you first and a pally can EASILY kill you =D)<br>
<br>
Rogues 1 on 1.... Give me a break... Easy as hell... Just don't let them catch you without a levitate ring and you'll survive.... (and be ready to use a sow potion / annul their sow potion if they decide they don't want to be pet kited by someone with jboots =D<br>
<br>
Shaman... Haven't ran into many of them in the past couple levels.... They have some nassty dots.... Careful, although it is a winnable fight.... You just have to use the pet to kill them.... summon companion / annul magic.... <br>
<br>
(I don't ever BO my pet in pvp (ok well never say never, I use BO INSTEAD of expediance in an indoor sitation)) But Don't cast more than 1 buff on your pet... summon companion and Annul are Always memmed to negate roots Summon Companion doesn't break root as far as I have experienced.... But it DOES allow you to dictate where they will be fighting you......<br>
<br>
Which is good =D<br>
<br>
Let's see how much more I can wring my brain out at 7:30 in the morning after a long day at work and a full nights of eq playing....<br>
<br>
Hit someone with a fire(or magic if you wanna test their resistances) based rain if you catch them medding.... =D Getting someone for 2 rains+ a bolt is a nasty way to start a fight....<br>
<br>
Well... in closing... I just wanted to say... I prefer indoors fighting.... (in a place where people can't cast through walls that is) pets = pwnage... Maybe this will change when I get velocity... but the fact that jboots is faster than expediance is just too much of a detriment to pvp...<br>
<br>
Maybe the new pet buff will be faster than jboots /shrug.. <p><center>Antarius Dominus<br>
